<h2 style="font-size: 22px;">Mt. Hood Community College</h2>
<strong>Gresham, OR</strong>

<div class="infolines">
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers credit for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers placement into higher-level courses for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-red">No</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>


<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>High school seniors who participate in the College Entrance Examination Board's AP (Advanced Placement) Program may seek advanced placement in a variety of disciplines. An entering freshman who has taken the AP tests should have the results sent to the Admissions and Records Office. The office of Admissions and Records and the Academic Advising and Transfer Center can provide interested students with procedures.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.mhcc.edu/Programs.aspx?id=1665" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

 <p class="box-padding-3">
    Additional restrictions and requirements may apply to the policy listed below. For more detailed information, visit the college's AP policy on the Web or contact the college directly.
 </p>

